[
    {
        "content": "<p>To help with <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"415254\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/415254-DRM/topic/ioctls.3A.20We.20should.20probably.20not.20pass.20Opaque.20to.20drivers/with/517557240\">#DRM &gt; ioctls: We should probably not pass Opaque to drivers</a>  it would be nice to automatically derive <code>FromBytes</code> on all uapi types. To do that it looks like we need to move <code>FromBytes</code> into its own crate so that <code>uapi</code> can depend on the crate that defines <code>FromBytes</code>. (Or we could define it in uapi I guess) Thoughts?</p>",
        "id": 524243264,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1750076328
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Looks like custom derives was added to <code>bindgen</code> in release 0.64:<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-bindgen/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md#0640\">https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-bindgen/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md#0640</a></p>",
        "id": 524244099,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1750076558
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I did this for Zeroable from pin-init</p>",
        "id": 524251690,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1750078880
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>oh, does that mean we already have Zeroable on uapi types?</p>",
        "id": 524251750,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1750078901
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, I picked it for 6.17</p>",
        "id": 524251835,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1750078924
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See the <code>pin-init-next</code> branch</p>",
        "id": 524251898,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1750078946
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Cool, I guess that I still need a new crate?</p>",
